'''List of Fellows and Residents of the American Academy in Rome''' is a list of those who have been awarded the [[Rome Prize]] or were Residents of the [[American Academy in Rome]].
The Rome Prize is a prestigious [[United States|American]] award made annually by the American Academy in Rome, through a national competition, to 15 emerging artists (working in Architecture, Landscape Architecture, Design, Historic Preservation and Conservation, Literature, Musical Composition, or Visual Arts) and to 15 scholars (working in Ancient, Medieval, Renaissance and early Modern, or Modern Italian Studies).<ref>[http://www.sof-aarome.org/sof_directories.html Directory by Year] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080416233433/http://www.sof-aarome.org/sof_directories.html |date=2008-04-16 }}, Society of Fellows</ref> Residents are selected from scholars and creative artists at a further stages in their career for shorter residencies at the American Academy. Some of these Residents are marked (R) in the table below.
