'''Seraband rug''' or '''Saraband''', is an [[Iran]]ian (Persian) [[weaving|handwoven]] floor rug from the Ser-e Band district (located southwest of [[Arak, Iran]]). These 19th-century and early-20th-century rugs have a "mir" design, characterized by small, pear or leaf forms in diagonal rows.

